{"article_id":"dnmAliZjarwwnDY8","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Today there is a national outcry about the murder of Ahmaud Arbery .","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"The public condemnation has forced a belated response .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"Those accused of his murder finally have been arrested .","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"His murder has become a global embarrassment for whites .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"For blacks , however , it is another humiliation , a continuing terror .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"It is the normal silence , however ,","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"that condemns thousands of African Americans to unjust deaths and millions to shattered lives .","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"When the camera turns away ,","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"the savage injustice","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"that embarrasses us","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"becomes simply business as usual .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Columnists","depth":2},{"id":12,"text":"In-depth political coverage , sports analysis , entertainment reviews and cultural commentary .","depth":3},{"id":13,"text":"The horror of Ahmaud Arbery ' s murder is now well known .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"The 25-year-old black man went for a jog down the middle of the street in the middle of the day on Feb. 23 .","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"Two white men decided","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"he was suspicious ,","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"hunted him down","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"and shot him point blank in the middle of the street at 1 p.m .","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"Local law enforcement had video evidence of the crime .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Yet no arrest was made until 74 days later , two months and two weeks after the murder .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Local authorities chose not to act .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"Two U.S. senators said nothing .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"The white church","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"- that had blessed slavery , segregation , apartheid in South Africa -","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"was silent .","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"Why did the arrests finally take place ?","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Because an intrepid reporter from the New York Times investigated the story","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"and made it public ;","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"the murder video was leaked to the public on the 72nd day after Ahmaud ' s murder .","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"As the public outrage grew ,","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"the arrests were made .","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"Never forget ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"as one commentator noted ,","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"they did not make the arrests","depth":15},{"id":35,"text":"because THEY saw the incriminating video .","depth":15},{"id":36,"text":"They made the arrests","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"because WE saw the video .","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"Embarrassed ,","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"faced with an aroused community and an international scandal ,","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"they finally acted .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"So it goes .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"African Americans suffer in silence the savage injuries of institutionalized racism .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"We live in northern ghettos","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"- driven there in the early part of the last century by terrorism -","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"most strikingly the Ku Klux Klan and their signature lynchings .","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"The Equal Justice Initiative reports","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"there were 4,084 lynchings of blacks in the South from 1877 to 1950 .","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"The Klan ,","depth":15},{"id":49,"text":"embraced by and often made up of the white gentry of the South ,","depth":15},{"id":50,"text":"often gathered at their churches","depth":15},{"id":51,"text":"to organize the public lynchings .","depth":15},{"id":52,"text":"They terrorized blacks","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"to end the fusion multiracial coalitions","depth":16},{"id":54,"text":"that grew up in the Reconstruction ,","depth":16},{"id":55,"text":"and to take back control of their states .","depth":15},{"id":56,"text":"The lynchings and violence were greeted with silence , if not approval .","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"White authorities , white churches , white society turned their heads ,","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"if they weren ' t applauding in approval .","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"Fleeing north ,","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"blacks were red lined into ghettos , with jobs hard to get ,","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"and discrimination closing doors .","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"To this day , African Americans are last hired and first fired .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"We suffer the worst poverty , the highest unemployment , the highest childhood hunger and malnutrition , the most inadequate health care .","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"This reality is sustained by the silence of white elites , the silence of the white church , the silence of the evangelicals , the silence of the best minded citizens .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"Then , the virus hits ,","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"and its most lethal effect is on those","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"who are vulnerable :","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"the elderly , the sick , the hungry , those with asthma and obesity .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"It hits hardest among the suddenly proclaimed \" essential workers \"","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"who do the work","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"that previously was largely \" invisible :","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"the bus drivers , the grocery clerks , the nurses and medical aides .","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"Not surprisingly , African Americans make up a disproportionate number of those killed or infected by the virus .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"The racial disparities are so stark","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"that they gain national and international attention .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"Pundits express shock and outrage at the reports ,","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"as if they were surprised by the results .","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"Editorials demand reform .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"Politicians call for action .","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"The informed public is embarrassed .","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"But little happens :","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"the rescue packages","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"passed by Congress","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"send most of the money to the biggest companies and the most affluent investors .","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"Banks are saved ;","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"the post office","depth":16},{"id":87,"text":"- with a largely minority workforce -","depth":16},{"id":88,"text":"is starved .","depth":15},{"id":89,"text":"Hunger spreads .","depth":15},{"id":90,"text":"Any expansion of food stamps is blocked .","depth":15},{"id":91,"text":"Arrested for leading nonviolent protests against segregation ,","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"Dr. Martin Luther King penned his letter from the Birmingham jail","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"expressing his grave disappointment with the \" white moderate \" and the \" white church. \"","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"He suggested","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"that the \" great stumbling block \" for African Americans","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"seeking their freedom","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"is \" not the White Citizen ' s Councilor or the Ku Klux Klanner , but the white moderate \"","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"who is more devoted to order than to justice. \"","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"He decried a religious community","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"\" largely adjusted to the status quo ,","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"standing as a tail-light behind other community agencies rather than a headlight","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"leading men to higher levels of justice . \"","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"The virus didn ' t discriminate .","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"The society enforced the discrimination ;","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"the virus just preyed upon its victims .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"We have gone too long ,","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"struggled too hard","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"to adjust to the reality","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"that it is dangerous to be black while jogging","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"or to be black in a pandemic .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"It isn ' t enough to express dismay","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"when the newspapers highlight the horrors .","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"We need leaders and citizens of conscience","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"who will act","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"and not rest","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"until justice is done .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":233,"left":127,"right":232,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":127,"left":119,"right":126,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":118,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":118,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":126,"left":120,"right":125,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":120,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":125,"left":121,"right":124,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":7,"right":123,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":123,"left":122,"right":10,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":122,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":232,"left":11,"right":231,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":231,"left":12,"right":230,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":230,"left":204,"right":229,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":204,"left":155,"right":203,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":155,"left":13,"right":154,"relation":"organiza